# Subordination, Non-Disturbance, and Attornment Agreement (SNDA)

Draft a tri-party SNDA that subordinates the lease to the lender, protects tenant possession on foreclosure, and requires attornment to the successor landlord.

## Prerequisites

1. Executed lease, including all amendments and any memorandum of lease.  
2. Loan documents: promissory note, mortgage or deed of trust, loan agreement, recorded documents.  
3. Property legal description and address; confirm leased premises lie within mortgaged property boundaries.  
4. Legal names of all parties, entity types, notice addresses, and signatory authority details.  
5. Status facts: tenant defaults, rent paid-through date, security deposit held, tenant improvement allowance, free rent periods, and option to renew or extend.  
6. Jurisdictional recording requirements and applicable notary forms.

## Output Structure / Process

- **A. Extract Facts Table**

| Term                         | Populate From            | Notes                                           |
|------------------------------|--------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Tenant Name                  | Lease                    | Confirm legal entity and address                |
| Lender Name                  | Loan Documents           | Use recorded lender info                         |
| Property Description         | Legal Description        | Verify accuracy and boundaries                   |
| Lease Premises               | Lease                    | Must be within property subject to mortgage     |
| Security Deposit Amount      | Lease                    | Confirm handling per SNDA provisions             |
| Tenant Default Status        | Lease Notices/Records    | Note any existing defaults or disputes           |
| Loan Documents Recorded Date | Public Records           | To verify priority status                         |

- **B. Draft Structure Table**

| Clause Section               | Must Include             | Options / Limits                                |
|------------------------------|--------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Recitals                    | Parties, Lease, Loan      | Include mortgage priority statement             |
| Definitions                 | Key terms (e.g., SNDA)   | Use consistent terminology                       |
| Subordination              | Lease subordinated       | Effective date, conditions                       |
| Non-Disturbance            | Tenant protection        | Exceptions, cure periods                          |
| Attornment                 | Tenant attorns to lender | Successor landlord duties                         |
| Representations & Warranties | Parties' authority       | Confirm signatory and existence                  |
| Lender Right to Cure       | Notice, cure periods     | Specify timing and methods                        |
| Lease Modification Limits  | Limits on tenant changes | Require lender consent                            |
| Notices                    | Addresses, delivery      | Include form and timing                           |
| Miscellaneous              | Governing law, venue     | Recording, execution, successor rights           |

- [ ] Confirm lease priority relative to mortgage.  
- [ ] Verify subordination is effective only upon fulfillment of non-disturbance conditions.  
- [ ] Ensure tenant’s security deposit and TI allowances are protected.  
- [ ] Check cure periods for tenant defaults and lender’s rights to cure.  
- [ ] Confirm attornment will be self-operative upon landlord transfer or foreclosure.  
- [ ] Verify governing law matches property's jurisdiction.  
- [ ] Confirm recording and notary requirements are met per local jurisdiction.  

```markdown
# Subordination, Non-Disturbance, and Attornment Agreement (SNDA)

## Recitals

- Parties: landlord, tenant, lender
- Lease description and date
- Loan description and recording info
- Purpose: subordinate lease to mortgage, protect tenant on foreclosure, require tenant attornment

## Definitions

- "Lease" means the lease agreement dated ____
- "Lender" means the holder of the loan secured by the mortgage
- "SNDA" means this agreement

## Subordination

- Tenant agrees lease is subordinate to lender mortgage
- Subordination effective only upon non-disturbance conditions met

## Non-Disturbance

- Lender agrees tenant may remain in possession if lender forecloses
- Tenant’s rights and obligations continue unchanged
- Security deposit and TI allowances protected

## Attornment

- Tenant agrees to attorn to successor landlord after foreclosure or transfer
- Attornment effective automatically upon transfer

## Representations and Warranties

- Parties have authority to execute
- Lease and loan documents are valid and enforceable

## Lender’s Rights to Cure

- Tenant to provide notice of default
- Lender allowed cure period of __ days to remedy defaults

## Lease Modification Limits

- Tenant may not modify the lease without lender consent

## Notices

- All notices sent to designated addresses by certified mail or courier

## Miscellaneous

- Governing law: state of ____
- Venue: courts of ____
- This agreement binding upon successors and assigns
- Agreement to be recorded where lease and mortgage are recorded
```

## Guidelines

- Do not expand tenant rights beyond the lease without lender consent; do not waive lender protections beyond usual standards.  
- Verify handling of security deposits consistent with lease and lender policies; protect tenant funds accordingly.  
- Ensure SNDA provisions only override conflicting lease terms, not entire lease obligations.  
- Confirm cure periods are adequate and enforceable under local law.  
- Use governing law of the property’s state; check state-specific recording and notary requirements.  
- Mark any uncertain citations or requirements with [VERIFY].  
- If lease is already subordinated, consider drafting nondisturbance and attornment provisions only.  
- Treat attornment as self-operative upon landlord transfers or foreclosure events.
